reviews.text: Its a newly renovated canteen with 2 muslim stall selling variety of food and my favourite is nasi tomato. But they do sell nasi ayam and nasi ayam penyet as well. Do support them when you have the chance!!

The nasi ayam penyet stall is the best, it is so nice that when others wants to order it is sold out. The cleanliness is tip top. And they are nice,sincere and funny. Do support, AYAM PENYET STALL‚ò∫Ô∏èüôèüèº.

The dishes
Nasi ayam, nasi tomato ,nasi sambal goreng. Sometimes there are mini breakfast prepared like currypuff and etc.

This canteen has changed owner last year and now sells Halal and Non-Halal food.

I love to eat their mee siam with telur mata lembu üòç.  You can also get fried rice, mee rebus and soto etc.  They have some kueh-kueh for breakfast too.

The next stall is nasi padang and I usually get the acar timun, beef rendang and kentang goreng ü•∞. They also sell nasi lemak daily and nasi briyani on Fridays.

Clean and aircon canteen. There are Malay Nasi Padang, and every Friday there will be Nasi Bryani.

Another malay stall have nasi ayam, nasi ayam penyet and on Friday, Nasi Sambal Goreng - either chicken or Paru. They do have mee rebus, mee soto, soto ayam, mee siam and kuih-kuih.

Then have Chinese chicken rice stall. The queue always long especially the soup. Don't take my words, you need to come and try it out.

And drink stalls too with friendly owner.
Everything about the nasi padang is nice , the details of the nasi padang is perfectly done . It tasted nice & never regret eating the nasi pandang , highly recommended.
